records.addlTxt:
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 1, maintain drug trafficking place. Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2 and 3, possess paraphernalia and obstruct officer.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for twenty-four (24) months.
Conditions of probation:
1) Complete sixty (60) hours community service (Drug related and community based);
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) Fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
5) Maintain absolute sobriety;
6) Pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
9) provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
10) spend sixty (60) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, stayed and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court.
Cash bail applied to court costs.
Minutes.
